The Mafdet harbor authority has received the final transit survey report and there is one obstacle remaining to all mineral transit through the Ember Crown: the Secondtooth Caldera Watcher has established permanent territorial control over the most direct approach corridor. This creature is not manageable through culling — it is a territory anchor of exceptional scale whose presence suppresses the entire approach zone's viability for bonded transit. The harbor authority has authorized an elimination contract.
The Secondtooth Caldera Watcher's territorial claim on the Ember Crown approach corridor has been broken. Mafdet harbor authority surveyors report that transit teams are moving through the previously blocked Secondtooth approach without obstruction, and the first bonded obsidian shipment from the Glasswash extraction zone has been logged at the harbor authority's mineral intake dock. The authority has named the now-clear approach corridor the Mafdet Transit Lane in the formal route registry.
